The party is not marked in red everywhere
In Hungary, the law defines exactly the holiday days and, around the holidays, it has become common to reorganize the working days whose number will decrease next year.
Holidays are not uniform in the EU and the United States either.
Hungarian legislation distinguishes between national and state holidays and rest days.
Rest days are often linked to religious festivals or important historical events.
In Hungary, we celebrate the new year, the last day of the year that ends and the first day of the new year are also days of rest, the latter especially so that the revelators can rest peacefully.
In addition, in a year, we have at least eleven celebrations marked in red.
March 15th is a national holiday, commemorating the revolution of 1848, as October 23rd is also the commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20th, we celebrate the constitution of our state, May 1st is the Labor Day, and on November 1st and 2nd, we remember the members of our family and our dead friends.
In addition, we have two days at Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
The days of our state, national or even religious holidays rarely fall on a weekend, according to the calendar, it has become common to reorganize the working days in cases where there is only one working day left before or after the party marked in red.
It is true that we pay the price for extended weekends by working or going to school on the Saturday before the extended weekend.
For many years, the Minister of Labour has made special regulations on the replacement days of the days preceding or following the holidays.
The Act covers all employers and employees, civil servants and persons working in the public service.
It does not apply, however, to service companies, institutions that rotate without interruption and in service, by virtue of their vocation, and also for days of rest.
This year, the working days will be changed only around the end of the year holidays: from December 24, life stops almost throughout the country because according to experience the majority of people do more overtime or take holidays that they have saved for these purposes in order to spend the days between Christmas and New Year's day at home.
Next year many holidays fall in the middle or the end of the week, so there will be fewer changes in workdays compared to this year.
The calendar will be reorganized the first time around the Labour Day to allow employees to stay at home four days in a row.
Saturday, April 25 will be a day of work to have a day of rest on Friday, May 2.
Another change is planned for October 23rd: Saturday, October 18th will be a working day replacing Friday, 24.
On the other hand, next year, the end of the year is announced under the sign of the holidays because from December 24, everyone will take a non-stop break even if the New Year's Day falls on a Wednesday.
