Cuba, the most beautiful island in the Caribbean
For visitors, it's really an island of freedom.
Everything you expect from your holidays can happen if you make a good choice.
Golden and white beaches like snow, high waves or then a calm sea like a pond.
Palms and all inclusive with servers offering you on the beach a pizza, ice cream or intoxicating cocktails.
Kitesurfing, golf and roulette.
On the islands of the Caribbean Sea, you will not find this list only in its entirety, but enriched.
However, there is only one island on which you will find much more and it is Cuba, the largest and most beautiful island in the Great Antilles.
By the time of the Spanish, Cuba had been the bastion of their invasion of America.
Christophe Columbus called it the most beautiful place the human eye has ever seen.
Havana has become the repository and the place of transshipment of the treasures that the Spanish had stolen and that they were transporting to Europe.
Then came the American era.
The Hotel Nacional was built in the early 1920s.
It was Lucky Luciano, one of the leaders of the American mafia, who had it built, since everything that was a crime in the USA (especially under prohibition) was admitted and supported in Cuba: drugs, gambling, prostitution.
Among his clients, there were, among others,
Winston Churchill, Ava Gardner, Frank Sinatra.
In Havana, tall buildings pushed and cars, belonging to the cult symbols of the 50's of the last century, were circulating on the wide boulevards.
Ernest Hemingway bought a property in San Francisco de Paula, near Havana, and in Cojímar he had his yacht.
The stars of the show business and politicians of the entire America left their signatures on the walls of the Bodeguita del Medio.
What about today?
You can leave your autograph on the walls of Havana's Bodeguita.
In the bar of the Hotel Nacional, a luxury hotel, you will be mixed the cocktail of your choice.
And these cult cars still circulate in Havana, since the jigoulis and fiats once imported have already long, in a climate so salty and humid, rotten.
Although Havana, especially the oldest part, is significantly decrepit, nowhere else in the vicinity are there as many splendid colonial monuments as there are right there.
Other places become more beautiful, for example Trinidad.
Since tourism brings the money if necessary, its development has the green light.
Over the past fifteen years, new hotels have pushed not only to Havana, but above all to Varader, on the coast of Holguín province, and also on small islands such as Cayo Coco, Cayo Guillermo and others.
Cuba still offers a fantasy that is unique in the world and that will be appreciated especially by lovers of small trains.
The cane had returned from the plantations extended in the sugar factories on a narrow track by small steam and motor trains.
Their rolling stock has not been renewed for decades, and this is how small locomotives can be seen in operation, whose contemporary ones are not only in museums elsewhere.
Where to direct his steps?
The majority of visitors do not miss the most well-known places.
So there is no need to write long about Varadero or Havana.
Otherwise remember that in the Hemingway property, already mentioned, there is a museum and that the one who loves this writer should not miss the visit.
The Viňales valley to the west of the island is one of the most picturesque corners of Cuba.
Exuberant vegetation grows there on limestone soil.
Mogotes, calcareous balloons and rocks go up in candle from the bottom of the valley, and, with fertile soil in their guts, even its rotten rocks are covered with a very dense vegetable carpet.
The valley is the place where Cuban tobacco is probably grown of the best quality.
You will be able to meet the final shape of this product if you visit one of the cigar factories in Havana.
Someone may also find it interesting that this is where Major Zeman's Chilean episode was shot.
Trinidad
Old town founded shortly after the Spanish colonized the island.
It was the slave trade and the sugar market that brought him glory and wealth.
Wealth has been embodied in the beauty and vitrine-city character of this small city.
Koloniální španělská architektura,výrazně ovlivněná pozdějšími francuzskými osadníky, if čtyři staletí teměř nezměnila.
Trinidad, located between the sea and the Escambray mountain massif, is a place so far away that still in the 50's of the last century, there was no road that would connect this region with the rest of the country.
This isolation allowed him to stay out of the way.
We didn't build anything, and that's why we didn't demolish anything either, everyone just had a roof over their head.
If you have more time in Trinidad than an afternoon, then it is worth seeing interesting places in the surrounding area, such as Playa Ancón Beach or the Sucreries Valley.
Then, in the evening, it is customary to go to the Casa de la Música, which is animated after sunset and where the music only gets dark in the early morning.
Barracks
Some refer to this village located in the far east of Cuba as the most beautiful of the island.
This view is certainly already influenced by the path that leads to it.
The two roads that lead there from Guantánamo must cross high and rugged mountains and cross a landscape almost without any signs of human activity.
UNESCO has listed Cuba's eastern echelon, thanks to its intact landscape, on the World Heritage List.
We make the best chocolate in the church, there is the cross of Christophe Columbus (in reality, it was born about a hundred years after the journey of Columbus) and from the hill where the old castle-fort and the current hotel El Castillo is held, we see several table mountains, the most famous of which is El Yunque.
About coffee, rum, cigars, the mountain massif Sierra Maestra, the Bay of Troves and Isla de Pinos, the Tropicana cabaret, the sanctuary of the patron saint of Cuba Caridad del Cobre, the Santeria, the African religions practiced by the descendants of the former slaves, about all this we could fill a number of pages.
