State debt will rise to one billion in 2009
The burden of a government debt in excess of CKr 84,000 is borne by each Czech.
At the end of September, total debt rose to CKr 842.7 billion.
The government had planned to borrow R$159.2 billion this year.
As a result of a better-than-expected government budget savings, the Department has reduced the planned amount to SEK 152.8 billion.
The debt of the State of the Czech Republic increased towards the end of September to CKr 842.7 billion.
During the nine months of this year it has therefore increased by 40.2 billion crowns.
