But I don't expect this change," he said.
Debts grow
The debt of the State is constituted by the debts of the central government and is generated mainly by the accumulation of deficits in the state budget.
The government debt is financed by treasury bonds, rent bonds, direct borrowings or, for example, by borrowings from the European Investment Bank.
The domestic debt of the state has increased this year from 38.5 billion to 719.4 billion kroner.
The foreign debt of the State has increased this year from SEK 1.7 billion to SEK 123.3 billion.
