What kind of insurance is it for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the event of an accident, involves a significant expenditure which will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, driving licence seniority, civil status, type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise takes the form of an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in exchange it becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a loss.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the rating to be paid.
It is for this reason that people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that these people have a lower disaster rate due to their caution.
Similarly, using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the probability of an accident.
By increasing the frequency the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
For this reason, the driver must study the situation in order to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
We will present here the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various disadvantages when entering into a contract with insurance at an affordable price, as can be the low experience in driving and driving licence seniority.
Although the ideal to be well insured is insurance at all risk, other more economical options exist.
The most likely drivers can opt for any risk insurance free of charge, so that they get insurance coverage at any risk but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the customer pays will be determined according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the amount will be lower," specifies Luis Noguera, the head in Spain of First Europa, online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and vehicle loss.
A piece of advice.
If you are under the age of 25 try to be careful and avoid claims to the extent possible, since this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the company's basic rate.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses, " explains Noguera.
Over the age of 25 this becomes easier for drivers when they enter into a contract with insurance, since the rate of claims is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is preferable to choose any risk insurance with frankness.
"Normally, young people cannot take advantage of the experience they have previously gained after an accident", says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, after passing the 'fear of the novice'.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children it is preferable for him to negotiate insurance at any risk, as long as his economic situation allows him.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be those with the lowest casualty rate, because increases will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be an insurance at all risk with franchise (which could be 300 euros), or an extended third-party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
"They have more casual driving and they have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury to assume a larger amount of franchises," Judge Luis Noguera.
For retirees, insurance at all risk is preferable with franchise (with this being 150 euros), or extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that motor insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents a major expense, that is why it is essential to study properly the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
